Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The minister of state for foreign affairs received 
a condolence cable from Faruq al-Shar', foreign minister of the 
fraternal Syrian Arab Republic, on the martyrdom of Na'ib 'Umran 
al-Ma'ayitah, counselor to the Jordanian Embassy in Beirut. 
  In his cable, al-Shar' said: I send to you my sincere 
condolences on the death of Na'ib 'Umran al-Ma'ayitah in a 
reprehensible crime. He added: I also offer my condolences to 
the al-Ma'ayitah family and ask God almighty to have mercy on 
the deceased and grant his family patience and comfort. 

